\subsection{Orientability of Clifford--Klein forms}
\label{subsec:ori}

Let $G$ be a Lie group, $H$ a closed subgroup of $G$, 
and $\Gamma$ a discrete subgroup of $G$ acting properly and freely on $G/H$. 
The local system of orientation of $\Gamma {\backslash} G/H$ is isomorphic to 
$\Gamma {\backslash} G {\operatorname*{\times}}_H {\mathbb{R}}$, where $H$ acts on ${\mathbb{R}}$ via 
$H \to \{ \pm 1 \}$, $h \mapsto {\operatorname{sgn}} \det {\operatorname{Ad}}_{{\mathfrak{g}}/{\mathfrak{h}}}(h)$. 
Thus, $\Gamma {\backslash} G/H$ is orientable if $H$ is connected. 

